    "Milton P. Horne": "In the creation story of Genesis\n1, the light that exists apart from the sun and moon is of a special\nnature. Readers will recall that in the opening of Qoheleth\u2019s\ninstruction the sun rises endlessly. At the conclusion of the sage\u2019s\nbook of instructions, the sun is finally darkening. Clouds cover the\nluminaries and may therefore also function as eschatological\nimagery.7\nThe real challenge of interpretation comes in vv. 3-",
    "Walter Brueggemann, Warren Carter": "6\n466"
